metadata.name: Canvas and Roller #2
metadata.description:
Many famous artists around the world use painting rolls in their works.
In this algorithm, the random effects of a painting roll are depicted on the canvas.
What is most noticed is the unpredictable effect that a paint roller can leave on the canvas which can be seen in real examples.
The viewer can also feel the combination of two or multiple rolls being passed over each other in the output of this algorithm.
Made by p5.js
press 's' to save original size

metadata.name: amongst the straight and narrow #111
metadata.description:
This project continues my exploration of attempting to simulate drawing with markers, this time on top of a more textured fabric-like surface. The marks themselves can range from highly ordered to highly disordered, with various intermediate states.

---

So let us wander far,
Amongst the straight and narrow.
For it is in the detours,
That we find our souls' marrow.

metadata.name: Obscure Archive #75
metadata.description:
Tabula rasa - we are all born without mental condition built-in, therefore knowledge and emotions come from experience.

As we grow up, emotions and feelings come to us naturally. Joy, sadness, anger, tranquility, confusion - to name a few, all these emotions makes us who we are today consciously or subconsciously. Yet, negative emotions are easier to remember and sticks longer compared to the positive ones.

Though, some people are lucky enough to be able to express their emotions freely to their surrounding, letting others know what they're feeling & what they've been through. While some other finds it harder to let go of those negative emotions. Wanting them to be gone but, alas, they can't find the right conditions to do so. Or even worse, these emotions get mixed up and tangled with their thoughts and memories making it harder to read or express.

__________

Obscure Archive is trying to capture what I (or maybe, you too) have been feeling constantly. These negative emotions is expressed and written as the text within the artwork, with the supergraphic representing thoughts & memories that we have. Some of the artwork has no overlay, just like those who can express their emotions freely. While some other have a completely different overlay, with messy text and supergraphic representing the concealment & entangled thoughts that make the emotions harder to read.

__________

made with ❤️ and p5js

metadata.name: Oddball #19
metadata.description:
Oddball is an expansion of the piece I created for day 7 of Genuary 2023. The prompt: Sample a color palette from your favorite movie/album cover. All seven palettes in this project were sampled from the album cover for Insolito by Tipper (https://tipper.bandcamp.com/album/insolito). 

The project title is a play on insolito meaning "unusual" and the featured bubble-like cellular noise. These bubbles are used to warp low-frequency simplex noise. When combined with the vibrant palettes, striking psychedelic patterns appear.

Controls:

[space] or click to toggle animation
[r] to reset animation to static view
[s] to save as 4000x4000 PNG
[t] to toggle paper texture

#genuary32nd

metadata.name: The Gap #15
metadata.description:
The Gap is an impressive generative art collection that showcases nature in its purest and most elemental form. At the center of the piece is a break between two walls of ice.
 The break appears to have been created by relentless ice pressure, and its shape and size are a result of the complex interaction between water, ice, and underlying geology.
But what truly captures the viewer's attention are the brilliant colors surrounding the break. The sky is depicted in a warm, brilliant color, while the break is depicted in a cold, brilliant color. These flat, saturated colors create a striking contrast that makes the break stand out in the landscape. Together, these colors create a vibrant and evocative atmosphere that invites viewers to dive into the landscape and explore its details.
In summary, The Gap is a unique work that combines technology and nature to create a stunning and impactful visual experience. With its contrast of warm and cold, brilliant flat colors, this work is a statement about the strength and simplicity of nature, and a call to action to protect our planet.

metadata.name: Less is More #15
metadata.description:
In this case, we tried to avoid abstract expressionist tendencies by removing personal scenarios.
Take a step back and let's create a geometrical work that intentionally avoids the usual conventional elements, focusing mainly on logic and physics concepts such as mathematical expansions and gravity.
In fact, we based our work and expression on the basis of simplicity and simple methods, as well as free from the usual philosophical or pseudo-philosophical complexity, and we concluded that by using simple geometric shapes, color, form, and material can be achieved in a pure manner.
Made by p5.js
press 's' to save original size

metadata.name: Subconscious #46
metadata.description:
It must have happened to you at some point that you had to wait while you also had access to paper and pen. Usually, you start drawing on paper in these situations. The pictures and drawings are often unclear, but you keep drawing them unconsciously, However, these aimless paintings are meaningful and reveal a little about your personality and mood.
The use of complex and angular lines in these unconscious paintings represents mental creativity moving towards a complex objective. There is an important issue and goal represented by these movements and twists.
These types of unconscious paintings represent hidden thoughts that emerge far beyond our conscious awareness, unearthing untold secrets about our personality; wishes, fears, and hidden desires that can never be expressed.
Most people do not consider these shapes to have meaning, only considering them to be scribbles that ruin papers and boxes. Nevertheless, every line you draw can be a representation of what's inside you and what's around you. These emoticons are like the DNA of the brain and never lie about what's on your mind; all you need to do is learn their language to understand hidden desires, wishes, fears, and dreams.
Made by p5.js

press 's' to save original size

metadata.name: RAUSCH #120
metadata.description:
RAUSCH is a series of generative artworks that explore imaginary digital architectures. 

This series challenges traditional notions of architectural representation and raises important questions about the role of resolution in design. Just as the pixel resolution of an image affects its perceived quality, the resolution of an architectural space can affect its qualities and livability. By embracing digital variation through codes, this series explores the interplay between abstract and concrete space through multiple resolutions. 

RAUSCH is inspired by the feeling of being overwhelmed by complex, chaotic and messy sensations, and aims to engage the viewer through a sense of wonder, disorientation, and awe.

Released on the occasion of Companions of Code, a group exhibition by VerticalCrypto Art at The NFT Gallery in London. 
Curated by Micol Ap. Exhibition 10-24 February 2023 

___________________________________________________
RAUSCH Controls:

Animation: 
• ‘1 - 2 - 3 - 4’ animate views
• 'MouseClick' pause/play animation

Functions:
(press key & wait)
• 'F' 24 FPS
• 'B' b/w mode 

Resize Canvas:
(press key & wait)
• '6' Portrait A4 - 1000x1414
• '7' Landscape 16:9 - 1920x1080
• '8' Portrait 9:16 - 1080x1920
• '9' Square 1:1 - 1024x1024
• 'DoubleClick' Fullscreen

Save & Export Image:
• 'S' save a .png of in current resolution

Save & Export GIF:
• 'G' save a 1-2 sec. seamless loop .gif of current view 
• 'P' save a 12-24 sec. seamless loop .gif of all the views
• 'T’ scale down current resolution, save a 12 sec. seamless loop .gif

Steps to save a gif/png :
• go in live/open mode (wait)
• resize canvas with 6,7,8, or 9 to your desired aspect ratio (wait)
• press S,G or P to save & download (wait) 
• enjoy RAUSCH :)

Save & Export GIF for social media sharing:
• go in live/open mode (wait)
• press T or G wait for recalculation & download. 
• enjoy RAUSCH 
• post on Twitter ;)

metadata.name: Echoes of Enough #49
metadata.description:
"Echoes of Enough" is a collection that explores self-worth, acceptance, and validation. The collection presents a visual representation of the struggles, doubts, and triumphs of recognizing our own value. Each piece delves into different aspects of ourselves and how they contribute to this feeling.

The seemingly chaotic yet orderly arrangement of the shapes in this collection reflects the tumultuous nature of the human experience. It speaks to the push and pull of self-doubt and the struggle to acknowledge one's own worth, while the raw and unrefined nature of the collection reflects the brutal reality of the human experience.

A hidden harmony beneath the surface represents the truth that we are all enough, just as we are. The collection invites the viewer to look within and acknowledge their own struggles and triumphs and to find comfort in the realization that the feeling of being enough is always present, like an echo that lingers. 

It is a reminder that we are enough, just as we are.



The artwork is fully created in javascript with the p5js library. 
The ideal viewing resolution is 1000x1000, and the artwork can be scaled to any size/resolution. The grain effect will fade slightly for higher resolutions.

metadata.name: Maps #11
metadata.description:
"The map is not the territory" (Alfred Korzybski)

Who has trodden the land of fxhash and tasted the soft breezes of Zancan's gardens? For those intrepid explorers of the realm of generative art, here are maps to guide you...

-----------------------------------
Press "s" to save the map image

Implemented in mainly plain javascript.
Inset images were generated programmatically by Clip-guided VQGAN (based on code by Katherine Crowson)
Uses the FastNoiseLite.js noise library
Uses Raymond Hill's Voronoi implementation to generate province/state boundaries
Uses the Fell Type Fonts by Igino Marini

metadata.name: Punktwelt #339
metadata.description:
Continuing on the theme of color perception in Farbteiler, Punktwelt is an exploration of color interaction, projection and perceived depth, and the aesthetics of simple Boolean operations on form.

Each shape is the result of a single block, a rectangular cuboid, subjected to a series of Boolean subtractions with other blocks, and rendered in parallel projection, oblique or axonometric, in the abstract landscape of the Punktwelt.

Some have horizons, some have banded or striped backgrounds. The unnatural drawing order and chromatic differences of the individual faces sometimes yields illusory or paradoxical visual geometries.

Press ’s’ to save a png. Press ’4’ to export a high resolution png. Press ’8’ to export a very high resolution png. Press ’e’ to export an SVG file (may take some time and produce large files).

Aspect ratio variations are 4:5, 5:4, 2:3, 3:2 and 1:1.

Built in Javascript with p5.js, p5.svg and csg.js.

metadata.name: Apophenia #45
metadata.description:
Apophenia is the art of seeing things in patterns that aren't 'really' there.
Frogs and tadpoles, small waving aliens, turtles, seahorses and bits of elephant - our brains will search for something we recognise in the randomness and chaos.
This pattern is made by tessellating hexagons. There are 12 unique hexagon possibilities plus reflections and rotations which bring the total possible for each placement in the design to 46.
Features include a choice of 7 colour palettes, 11 scales and the drawing of a grid behind the main pattern or not. Most rare are the very large or small scale with grid lines in a colour that isn't Teal and Peach.
